Text: Gimme my money back, you dumbass!
An unconscious Gonzales is showered with boo's.
One...no, two shots to the chin...
Well, I think you get the idea now.

You can predict the outcome with battle data, but
these contests are not an absolute science.
Wh-Whoa... You even knew this might happen...!

Heh... I'll let you in on a little secret: there are
two ways to win at betting.

The first is to put your money on the fighter with
the higher battle power.

The second is to seek out the weakest competitor
and then bet on whoever they go up against.

Tomorrow are the fourth-round matches. And Mundane
Mann with his 28 battle power is fighting...
Moi, the Victorious Golden Dragon, Goldy Gilded.

Heh... Think you have what it takes to solve the
victory formula?

Aw, c'mon, Cid! There's a match I absolutely can't
lose tomorrow, so lend me everything ya got, I'm
beggin' ya!

You know you're gonna regret it, so just gimme some
funds and...

(Heheh... This is excellent. He's acting like maybe
it wasn't just chance.)
Gotta make sure to let 'em down hard tomorrow, too.
Right?! Gotta let 'em down, so...gimme some cash!
I suddenly hear Skel yelling and pounding on my door.
I unlock the door and let him in.

Rose, the student council president, stabbed her
fiance Perv Asshat and is on the run!
